President Trump delivered remarks during his visit to Japan as the nation's first state guests following the enthronement of Emperor Naruhito. He expressed gratitude for the hospitality and warm welcome received in Japan and conveyed the good wishes of the American people for the alliance between the two countries. Trump also mentioned the meeting with Emperor Naruhito and Empress Masako, as well as the close partnership with Prime Minister Shinzo Abe. He noted that the name of Japan's new Imperial Era, Reiwa, symbolizes beautiful harmony and unity. Trump emphasized the importance of embracing the potential for cooperation in various areas, such as technology, space, infrastructure, defense, commerce, and diplomacy. He also highlighted the need to pass on the alliance as a gift to future generations. Trump concluded by expressing his best wishes for a peaceful and prosperous Reiwa Era.